      "id": "step-6-c-runtime",
      "title": "C Runtime (Fibers, HTTP, WebSockets)",
      "description": "The performance-critical runtime is written in C with security hardening flags. A fiber layer powers lightweight concurrency, HTTP and WebSocket modules provide networking, and a system layer handles OS interactions. Compiled LLVM IR links against these libraries.",
